HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1044
By Vital
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Coy Richard Tinsley of
Harrison.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Coy Richard Tinsley of Harrison; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Tinsley was an exemplary public servant and consummate professional
who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in numerous
capacities; and
WHEREAS, Coy Tinsley was born on June 6, 1947, in Cleveland and enlisted in the
U.S. Army on March 30, 1968; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Tinsley completed basic training at Fort Campbell, Kentucky, in June
1968 before attending advanced individual training as an infantryman at Fort Campbell; he
completed NCO Candidate training at the U.S. Army Infantry School at Fort Benning, Georgia,
in November 1968; and
WHEREAS, he then deployed to South Vietnam as a rifleman with Company E, 4th
Battalion of the 3rd Infantry Regiment, in January 1969; he was captured and taken as a prisoner
of war on March 9, 1969, and remained in captivity for 242 days, until November 5, 1969; and
WHEREAS, after his release, Coy Tinsley was briefly hospitalized at Fort Campbell to
recover from his injuries; he went on to serve as a senior rifleman with the Field Support
Company at the U.S. Army Chemical School at Fort McClellan, Alabama, from January 1970
until he left active duty on March 29, 1971; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Tinsley received his honorable discharge once his inactive reserve
service was completed on March 1, 1974; he then began his career as a truck driver and
worked for the United States Postal Service, retiring after thirty years; and
